wrdo.name: Hand Sanitizer
wrdo.health_summary: Hand sanitizer is effective at killing germs and bacteria on the skin, helping to prevent the spread of infections. It is a convenient alternative to hand washing with soap and water, especially when those resources are not available. However, it is important to note that hand sanitizer is not effective against all types of germs, such as norovirus, and it does not remove dirt or grime. Frequent use of hand sanitizer can also dry out the skin, so it is important to moisturize regularly.
wrdo.short_report: Hand sanitizer is a convenient way to kill germs on your hands, but it's not a substitute for washing with soap and water.

wrdo.name: Nasal Spray
wrdo.health_summary: Nasal spray is primarily used for relieving nasal congestion and dryness. It typically contains a saline solution and may include preservatives. It has minimal nutritional value and is not a significant source of calories, protein, carbs, or fats.
wrdo.short_report: Nasal spray provides temporary relief from nasal congestion and dryness but offers no nutritional benefits.

wrdo.name: Wonder Mist Air Freshener
wrdo.health_summary: This is an air freshener and not intended for consumption.
wrdo.short_report: Consuming this will not freshen your breath, but might require a trip to the hospital.

duelistinstalocker.name: Tiger Biscuits
duelistinstalocker.health_summary: Tiger biscuits are a processed snack food that is high in sugar, fat, and calories, and low in essential nutrients. Regular consumption may contribute to weight gain and other health issues.
duelistinstalocker.short_report: Tiger biscuits are a processed snack with high sugar and fat content, offering limited nutritional value.
